title: Yorktown Wrestling Club traveling to Pa.
text:
Yorktown Wrestling Club traveling to Pa. The Star Press 3:56 p.m. EDT October 7, 2015 Cael McCormick CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
WOMEN’S TENNIS 
Former Yorktown coach Jini Morgan led Taylor to a 6-3 victory over Spring Arbor University in the Crossroads League Tournament quarterfinal. Taylor’s Corinne Hoffman and Betsy Jones both fought through three-set battles to win their singles courts. Jones and senior Rachel Kammer won at No. 2 doubles, 8-6, after losing previously during the regular season matchup. 
WRESTLING 
The Yorktown Wrestling Club is sending a team to compete at the Columbus Day Duals in York, Pennsylvania, starting Saturday. Ten Yorktown wrestlers are on the all-star team comprised of wrestlers from six different wrestling clubs in Indiana. The team’s official name on www.trackwrestling.com is “Hoosier Hustle”. The Yorktown wrestlers participating are Zachary Todd , Brayden Curtis , Joshua Stephenson , Xayvier Curtis , Alex Barr , Colt Rutter , Cael McCormick , Brad Laughlin , Ryan Brewer and Jacob Rhoades . 
RUNNING 
The Randolph County YMCA will host a Halloweek 5K run and walk at 6 p.m. Thursday, Oct. 29. The entry fee is $20. Those who pre-register are guaranteed an event T-shirt. A prize will be awarded to the runner with the best costume, but dressing up is optional. Read or Share this story: http://tspne.ws/1Rt7B3F TOP VIDEOS
